# INTERNAL LIQUIDITY - Trading Notes Screenshot

## Visual Content Description

### Chart Layout
Two identical price charts stacked vertically showing candlestick patterns with the following elements:

---

## TOP CHART

**Price Action:**
- Strong uptrend on left side reaching "Dealing Range High"
- Downtrend through middle section
- Consolidation period (highlighted in gray box)
- Recovery/uptrend on right side
- Final consolidation and slight decline at far right

**Key Levels:**
- Dealing Range High (marked at top left)
- Horizontal support/resistance zones marked across chart

---

## BOTTOM CHART

**Annotations & Labels:**

1. **"Dealing Range High"** (top left area)

2. **"High - Lower high close to it makes it a low resistance high."** (left side, with downward arrow indicator)

3. **"BSLQ"** label (middle-left area)

4. **"*Clean* low resistance highs = Asia Session High BS Liquidity"** (center annotation with cursor icon)

5. **"BMS"** label (lower right area)

6. **"Dealing Range Low"** (bottom right)

**Additional Markers:**
- **"FVG"** with cursor icon (middle-right area)
- **"MT"** label (top right)
- **"OB"** label (top right, below MT)

**Price Structure:**
- Same overall pattern as top chart
- Multiple liquidity zones highlighted in gray boxes
- Clear marking of dealing range boundaries
- Annotations focus on internal liquidity concepts

---

## Header Elements
- **"INTERNAL LIQUIDITY"** (bold text, top left)
- **"BLESSED TRADER."** logo/watermark (top center)
- Subtitle: "Your guide to consistency in the industry of chaos."

---

## Key Concepts Illustrated
- Dealing Range High/Low identification
- Low resistance highs
- Buy Side Liquidity (BSLQ/BMS)
- Fair Value Gaps (FVG)
- Order Blocks (OB)
- Market Type (MT)
- Clean liquidity levels from Asia Session
